{"turn": 12, "stop_reason": "end_turn", "usage": {"in": 2, "out": 1734, "cache_read": 21968, "cache_write": 1613}, "blocks": [{"signature": "", "thinking": "", "type": "thinking"}, {"text": "# Executive Summary: Spring Glow Creative Campaign\n\n**Campaign:** Spring Glow Campaign Execution (\"SGX\") \u2014 Lumina Beauty Corp\n**Hero Product:** GlowSerum\n**Delivering Team/Agency:** Northstar Media Pty Ltd's Campaign Department, led by Creative Director Zoe Beaumont (*source: project_update_0886_372.md*, Northstar Media project update, 2026-06-11), with production support from **Melbournescope Studios**, the external creative production vendor confirmed for concept development and delivery (*source: memo_0778_234.md*, SGX Budget Allocations & Vendor Updates, 2026-02-07).\n\n---\n\n### 1. Total Spend on Creative Work\n\nTwo source documents provide budget figures, and they do not fully reconcile \u2014 both are cited here for transparency:\n\n- **Itemized creative cost sheet** (*source: spring_glow_budget.csv*) lists line-item spend of:\n - Media: $25,000\n - Production: $15,000\n - Agency: $8,000\n - Talent: $5,000\n - Printing: $1,200\n - **Total: $54,200**\n\n- **SGX program budget memo** (*source: memo_0778_234.md*, Feb 2026) cites a broader total SGX budget of **AUD 385,000**, of which **AUD 120,000** is allocated specifically to \"creative production\" (the remainder \u2014 AUD 150,000 digital media and AUD 115,000 analytics/audience research \u2014 falls outside creative work).\n\n*Note for leadership:* These two figures come from different planning documents (an itemized cost sheet vs. a higher-level allocation memo) and were not found to reconcile in the available records. The creative-production-specific figure most directly answering \"creative work spend\" is either the **$54,200** itemized total or the **$120,000** creative-production allocation cited in the February 2026 memo \u2014 this should be verified against final Wattle Accounting invoices before external reporting (status reports note the final invoice was still pending client review as of Dec 2025, *sources: status_report_0674_480.md and .txt*).\n\n### 2. Creative Concepts Approved\n\n- **Core creative message/tagline:** \"Reawakening Your Natural Radiance,\" positioning GlowSerum as an essential seasonal-revitalization ritual (*source: brief.txt*, Campaign Brief: Spring Glow Launch Strategy, Sarah Chen, VP Marketing Strategy, Oct 26, 2023).\n- **Approved deliverables confirmed in execution-phase status reports:**\n - TVC (video) visuals \u2014 internally approved, with only minor adjustments requested (*source: status_report_0674_480.md / .txt*, Sarah Chen, Head of Campaign Management, Dec 2025).\n - Digital assets and influencer-partnership content \u2014 finalized and received client approval (*source: project_update_0886_372.md* and *_v1.txt*, June 2026).\n - Print assets \u2014 approved with a minor scheduling delay noted (*source: status_report_0674_480_v1.md*).\n- No single itemized list of named \"Concept A/B/C\" options was found in the available documents; the approvals on record are for the tagline/message direction and the resulting TVC, digital, and print asset executions built on it.\n\n### 3. Who Delivered the Work\n\n- **Northstar Media Pty Ltd** \u2014 the agency of record running SGX end-to-end (email domain and staff, e.g., Kenji O'Brien, Ethan Silva; project reporting authored by Northstar staff \u2014 *sources: email_1354_865.eml, project_update_0886_372.md*).\n- **Zoe Beaumont, Creative Director, Campaign Department (Northstar Media)** \u2014 signed off on the June 2026 SGX creative project update.\n- **Melbournescope Studios** \u2014 external production vendor confirmed for concept work, with concept approvals targeted for 2026-02-15 (*source: memo_0778_234.md*).\n\n---\n\n**Recommendation:** Reconcile the two conflicting budget figures ($54,200 itemized vs. $120,000/$385,000 memo) with Wattle Accounting's final invoice before this summary is distributed externally, and confirm with Melbournescope Studios/Northstar Media whether additional named creative concept options exist beyond the approved tagline and asset set documented above.", "type": "text"}]}
